# NAME: Claude
# AUTHOR: Sisyphus (generated for tangjunhua1993/rule)
# REPO: https://github.com/tangjunhua1993/rule
# UPDATED: 2026-04-19
# DESCRIPTION: Route Claude / Anthropic related hosts through proxy. Keep broad CDN rules commented to avoid proxying unrelated traffic.
# DOMAIN: 4
# DOMAIN-SUFFIX: 4
# TOTAL: 8

# Anthropic / Claude core
DOMAIN-SUFFIX,anthropic.com
DOMAIN,api.anthropic.com
DOMAIN,console.anthropic.com

DOMAIN-SUFFIX,claude.ai
DOMAIN-SUFFIX,claude.com
DOMAIN-SUFFIX,claudeusercontent.com
DOMAIN,platform.claude.com

# Common analytics/cdn observed in some setups (kept, originally present)
DOMAIN,cdn.usefathom.com

# ---------------------------
# Optional / CAUTION:
# Uncomment only when you have verified Claude uses these exact subdomains.
# Broad cloud/CDN suffixes will route a lot of non-claude traffic through your proxy.
# ---------------------------
# DOMAIN-SUFFIX,cloudfront.net
# DOMAIN-SUFFIX,amazonaws.com
# DOMAIN-SUFFIX,cdn.cloudflare.net
# DOMAIN-SUFFIX,googleusercontent.com

# NOTES:
# - After deploying this, open browser DevTools while using Claude (web/console) and add any missing hosts you observe to this list.
# - Prefer exact DOMAIN or DOMAIN-SUFFIX entries for specific subdomains rather than broad cloud/CDN wildcard rules.
